{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"Thanks for moving things forward Aki \u2764\ufe0f\r\n\r\nI'm think we should only use javascript modules in webgl2 examples. As far as I'm aware, any browser\/platform that supports webgl2 also supports javascript modules.\r\n\r\nI like the `jsm` folder. Do you this it's possible to automate this? Can we create\/add a script in `utils` that converts all `examples\/js` files to `examples\/jsm` (or the other way around)?\r\n","created_at":"2018-12-28T17:20:47.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/15482#issuecomment-450395219","id":450395219,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15482","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ1MDM5NTIxOQ==","updated_at":"2018-12-28T17:20:47.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/450395219","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"Actually, I'm not sure what I prefer...\r\n\r\n```\r\nexamples\/js\/OrbitControls.js\r\nexamples\/jsm\/OrbitControls.js\r\n```\r\n\r\nOr\r\n\r\n```\r\nexamples\/js\/OrbitControls.js\r\nexamples\/js\/OrbitControls.module.js\r\n```\r\n\r\nI think I prefer the later.","created_at":"2018-12-28T17:48:44.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/15482#issuecomment-450399427","id":450399427,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15482","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ1MDM5OTQyNw==","updated_at":"2018-12-28T17:48:44.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/450399427","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"> I like the jsm folder. Do you this it's possible to automate this? Can we create\/add a script in utils that converts all examples\/js files to examples\/jsm (or the other way around)?\r\n\r\nThere has been a lot of discussion on that topic. There are some solutions that are good enough but don't work on all examples. Some examples just have to be handled manually. Cloth.js, for example, has half of its simulation logic in the html file making it nearly impossible to convert automatically. I'm not sure how many examples are like that.\r\n\r\n>I think I prefer [.module.js]\r\n\r\nIt appears that accepted convention is .jsm extension. How do you feel about that?","created_at":"2018-12-28T18:02:15.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/15482#issuecomment-450401520","id":450401520,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15482","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ1MDQwMTUyMA==","updated_at":"2018-12-28T18:02:15.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/450401520","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/708984?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/arodic","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcwODk4NA==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"arodic","type":"User","id":708984,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"@mrdoob are you suggesting that there should be both modules and non-modules side-by-side? Personally, I think that would be too much bloat in the repo. Having modules only is much cleaner and future oriented - but that would mean not supporting [non es6 browsers such as IE and Samsung Internet](https:\/\/caniuse.com\/#search=modules).\r\n\r\nI'm afraid I don't have a solution for that problem. Let's keep the discussion going.\r\n\r\nThis PR is to demonstrate that once we are ready to go full modules and pull the plug on IE et al, there is a path forward with manual and incremental conversion.","created_at":"2018-12-28T18:20:57.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/15482#issuecomment-450404400","id":450404400,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15482","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ1MDQwNDQwMA==","updated_at":"2018-12-28T18:20:57.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/450404400","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/708984?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/arodic","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcwODk4NA==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"arodic","type":"User","id":708984,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"> Cloth.js, for example, has half of its simulation logic in the html file making it nearly impossible to convert automatically.\r\n\r\nThat's fair. Maybe we should start by converting files that people really need though. Loaders, Controls, etc\r\n\r\n> It appears that accepted convention is .jsm extension. How do you feel about that?\r\n\r\nI do not like the jsm extension. Web servers need additional mime types so these get gzipped. That's why I went with `three.module.js`.","created_at":"2018-12-28T18:50:18.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/15482#issuecomment-450408708","id":450408708,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15482","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ1MDQwODcwOA==","updated_at":"2018-12-28T18:50:18.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/450408708","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"> @mrdoob are you suggesting that there should be both modules and non-modules side-by-side? Personally, I think that would be too much bloat in the repo. Having modules only is much cleaner and future oriented - but that would mean not supporting non es6 browsers such as IE and Samsung Internet.\r\n\r\nYeah, I think it'll be better to keep both modules and non-modules for now. I think it's a little bit too early to completely switch. It needs a bit of transition.","created_at":"2018-12-28T18:53:07.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/15482#issuecomment-450409109","id":450409109,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15482","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ1MDQwOTEwOQ==","updated_at":"2018-12-28T18:53:07.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/450409109","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Hey @mrdoob, I'm lurking on this PR because I was one of the posters on the other #9562 issue trying to figure out how to get the loader examples to work with the bundler I'm using (Parcel).   I even made a PR on @arodic's branch to convert the `OBJLoader`.  So first, I wanted to say thanks for joining in the conversation and considering this.  \r\n\r\nIt's not clear what the outcome is here, clearly the PR is dead but you say \"better to keep both modules and non-modules for now\", so is the plan (e.g. for Loaders) to keep duplicate copies of the source in both module and non-module form?  \r\n\r\nIf that's the case then I wonder if there's a way forward on this that doesn't cause the code to diverge between the two versions (modular vs not) of the same file.   I had the impression here that @arodic was doing this PR somewhat manually, but there was some discussion about automating it, so perhaps there's a way to do the conversion automatically in such a way that when a bugfix is made to the main (non-modular) version, it gets propagated automatically to the modular script by running the automated conversion.  \r\n\r\nI'm not sure if @ltee from the `three-full` repo has been part of these discussions in the past or if he's just doing his own thing on the side, but he appears to have some stuff [NodeJS scripts](https:\/\/github.com\/Itee\/js-to-es\/blob\/master\/sources\/js-to-es.js) for this,  ([discussion](https:\/\/github.com\/Itee\/three-full\/issues\/1)).  Maybe that's something that can be leveraged.","created_at":"2018-12-30T00:18:39.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/15482#issuecomment-450530345","id":450530345,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15482","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ1MDUzMDM0NQ==","updated_at":"2018-12-30T00:18:39.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/450530345","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/uglycoyote\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/uglycoyote\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/2461007?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/uglycoyote","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/uglycoyote\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/uglycoyote","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/uglycoyote\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI0NjEwMDc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/uglycoyote\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/uglycoyote\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/uglycoyote\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"uglycoyote","type":"User","id":2461007,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/uglycoyote\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/uglycoyote\/orgs"}},{"index":7,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"> Yeah, I think it'll be better to keep both modules and non-modules for now. I think it's a little bit too early to completely switch. It needs a bit of transition.\r\n\r\nThis is understandable. However, having two versions in `examples\/`(source) is a little bit confusing and similar idea was rejected before when discussing #14447 (shaderchunks to ES6 modules). I think it would make more sense to have examples(source) in ES6 module format and then have a build step that generate say `three.examples.js` same like the rest of three.js codebase. This is also not ideal (big file) but perhaps it is acceptable for transition period?","created_at":"2018-12-31T02:15:36.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/15482#issuecomment-450601669","id":450601669,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15482","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ1MDYwMTY2OQ==","updated_at":"2018-12-31T02:15:36.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/450601669","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/events{\/privacy}","avat